            <title>[LU-14844] mgc_requeue_timeout_min is missing on old lustre version</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14844</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the landing of&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14516&quot; title=&quot;make mgc&amp;#39;s wait-before-reprocess configurable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14516&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14516&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the test-framework on startup uses&#160;mgc_requeue_timeout_min to decrease the run time of test. This value doesn&apos;t exist for earlier lustre version which breaks interop testing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
